Peru Stocks: Casa Grande, Credicorp, Ferreyros, Maple, Volcan

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-07-11T17:35:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-11/peru-stocks-casa-grande-credicorp-ferreyros-maple-volcan.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 1:05 p.m. New York time.  The Lima General Index dropped 0.3 percent to 19,862.57.
The MSCI All Peru Capped Index fell 1.4 percent to 2,514.94.  Industrial and banking stocks dropped after U.S. shares
declined on concern over Europe’s debt crisis, said Omar
Delgado, a trader at Lima-based Juan Magot y Asociados SAB.  Ferreyros SA (FERREYC1)  (FERREYC1 PE), the Lima-based distributor for
Caterpillar Inc., plunged 9 percent to 2.44 soles.  Maple Energy
Plc. (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas producer with operations
in Peru, fell 3 percent to 96 cents after crude declined for a
second day in  New York .  Credicorp Ltd. (BAP)  , Peru’s largest
financial services company, slid 2.4 percent to $84.93.  Casa
Grande  (CASAGRC1 PE), Peru’s largest sugar producer, fell 1
percent to 14.90 soles after futures declined in New York.  Copper, zinc and tin miners dropped after the metals
declined in New York and  London .  Panoro Minerals Ltd. (PML)  , a Canadian copper and gold
exploration company, fell 2.1 percent to 47 cents. Volcan Cia
Minera SAA (VOLCABC1 PE), Peru’s largest zinc producer, declined
1.4 percent to 2.87 soles.  Minsur SA (MINSURI1)  (MINSURI1 PE), the world’s
fourth-largest tin producer, fell 1.1 percent to 3.45 soles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in  Lima  at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  